                <Header>Freedom of Information Act (FOIA)</Header>
                <Paragraph>Like all Federal agencies, the TVA is required to disclose records that any person requests in writing. The statute contains, however, nine exemptions and three exclusions that may shield some records or parts of them from disclosure. The TVA operates a FOIA requester service center. Phone, 865-632-6945.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
            <EntitySourceOfInformation EntitySourceOfInformationId="2951" SortOrder="14">
                <FooterDetails>
                    <Email/>
                    <Footer/>
                    <WebAddress>https://www.tva.com/Energy/Valley-Renewable-Energy/Green-Power-Providers</WebAddress>
                </FooterDetails>
                <Header>Green Power</Header>
                <Paragraph>The Green Power Providers program offers Tennessee Valley homeowners and businessmen and women an opportunity to help the TVA generate clean, renewable energy. Participants in the program agree to install a small-scale renewable energy system on their property, and the TVA pays them for every kilowatt hour generated by that system.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
